      "TargetSubject": "Science",
      "Text": "#### Driving Question(s):\n1. What makes humans and other animals perceive something as beautiful?\n2. How can we mathematically measure objects or images in ways that capture what a viewer would describe as “beautiful”?\n\n#### Essential Question(s):\nHow can science help deepen our understanding of the Arts, Humanities, and ourselves?",
      "Tags": [
        {
          "Value": ""
        }
      ],
      "LearningObj": "1. Interpret a concept map of how our perception of beauty results from interactions between our brain, sensory systems, and the environment.\n2. Calculate and interpret two mathematical measures of beauty: symmetry and prototypicality (i.e. averageness).\n3. Create a list of factors that affect what people perceive as beautiful.",
